parameterizeURI

public static String parameterizeURI(String uri,
                                     Map<String,String> parameters)
Parameterizes the given URI, which is expected not to have any parameters yet. The parameters from the map are used to add parameters to the URI (map key becomes parameter name and corresponding map value becomes the parameter value).

Parameters:
uri - The URI to parameterize. It is taken as-is, but should not contain any parameters yet. May be null.
parameters - Parameters to add to the URI. Both keys and values will be escaped before added to the URI. May be null or empty.
Returns:
The parameterized URI. At least an empty string (never null), if parameters were empty.

getFileStream

public static final InputStream getFileStream(URL fileURL,
                                              String filePath)
Tries to get input stream from:
  1. the fileURL
  2. the filePath when the previous failed.

Parameters:
fileURL - The URL pointing to a file, which may also be located outside the current machine. May be null.
filePath - The path to a file. May be null.
Returns:
The resolved input stream or null.
Since:
2.0

Parameters:

Returns:
The encoded version of the URI component.
